                  <persName id="t17491209-60-person456">
                  Robert 
                  Turner 
               <interp inst="t17491209-60-person456" type="surname" value="Turner"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17491209-60-person456" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17491209-60-person456" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 17th October in the evening, coming down <placeName id="t17491209-60-crimeloc269">Cheapside</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17491209-60-crimeloc269" type="placeName" value="Cheapside"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17491209-60-crimeloc269" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17491209-60-off267 t17491209-60-crimeloc269"></join>; I felt a pull at my pocket; I turned about, and put my hand in my pocket, I felt my handkerchief; Hutton was at my elbow, the other was two yards behind me; I suspected them both by their countenances, I did not take any notice of it; then the tall fellow Hutton walked by me, the other kept behind, Hutton went over the way, the other followed him at some distance; after they were gone, I went cross the way behind the coaches, and saw them join company, they went down the Poultery, I followed them: they turned down by the mansion house, and up Bucklers Bury, and from thence into Cheapside again, I followed them, and observed them to converse together as they walked. In Cheapside I called a man to my assistance, and I took hold of one, and he the other: we carried them into the Magpye and Horshoe; we sent for a constable, who is since dead; they were searched, and about 7 or 8 handkerchiefs were found upon Smith, mine being one of them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17491209-60-person457">
                  John 
                  Bolton 
               <interp inst="t17491209-60-person457" type="surname" value="Bolton"></interp>
